text: <!channel> In preparation for next week's Apple announcement I started adapting my Photoshop Android export script to also export iOS assets.
Don't know what the new sizes or scale factors will be but I built it so we can change it on the fly after the announcement and ship it with a blog post.
Just FYI in case you're working on an iOS project that may need assets scaled to whatever new sizes they announce next week. Would love to use your PSDs to test the script.
<!channel> has anyone else had problems in photoshop with copying text and it pastes at a totally different size?
and if so, have you been able to resolve it??
In newer versions of PS, if you copied the text from another text layer it will past it with the original size.

If that makes any sense. I always have a text editor to quickly paste the text there and copied it without style info. Although I remember reading somewhere that there may be a key combo to copy and strip styles.
